President Obama will host Prime Minister Shinzo Abe of Japan for an official visit to the White House on April 28. The visit will include a State Dinner in the evening. The purpose of the visit is to celebrate the strong global partnership between the United States and Japan that has developed over the past 70 years since the end of World War II. The leaders will also highlight the common values and principles that have made the bilateral relationship enduring. The topics of discussion will include economic, security, and global issues such as progress on the Trans Pacific Partnership, Japan's expanding role in the Alliance, and climate change.